Abstract: Generally prohibits arbitration of child custody or visitation agreements.
Proposed law (R.S. 9:4216) provides that arbitration of child custody or visitation is against
the public policy of this state and any provision of an agreement to arbitrate that mandates
the arbitration of child custody or visitation is void and unenforceable.
Proposed law prohibits state courts from recognizing or enforcing any arbitral award
governing child custody or visitation.
